</mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>639</anchor> <rss>jms-00J5.rss.xml</rss>  <addr>jms-00J5</addr>  <route>jms-00J5.xml</route> <date><year>2024</year> <month>1</month> <day>18</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> <contributor><link href="marcelofiore.xml" type="local" marcelofiore="addr">Marcelo Fiore</link></contributor></authors> <title>Visualising <link href="jms-00I7.xml" type="local" addr="jms-00I7" title="Relation">relations</link></title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>640</anchor> <rss>jms-00IL.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Exercise</taxon> <addr>jms-00IL</addr>  <route>jms-00IL.xml</route> <date><year>2024</year> <month>1</month> <day>17</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> <contributor><link href="marcelofiore.xml" type="local" marcelofiore="addr">Marcelo Fiore</link></contributor></authors> <title>An internal diagram</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Draw the <link href="jms-00IK.xml" type="local" addr="jms-00IK" title="Internal diagrams of relations">internal diagram</link> corresponding to the following <link href="jms-00I7.xml" type="local" addr="jms-00I7" title="Relation">relation</link>:</p><tex display="block">
  \begin {aligned}
   S&amp; \colon \mathbb {Z} \mathbin { \nrightarrow } \mathbb {Z} \\ 
   S&amp;=  { \mathopen {} \left \{ 
     { \mathopen {} \left ( 1,0 \right ) \mathclose {}} ,
     { \mathopen {} \left ( 1,2 \right ) \mathclose {}} ,
     { \mathopen {} \left ( 2,1 \right ) \mathclose {}} ,
     { \mathopen {} \left ( 2,3 \right ) \mathclose {}} 
    \right \} \mathclose {}} 
  \end {aligned}
</tex></mainmatter> </tree></mainmatter> </tree></context> <related><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>641</anchor> <rss>jms-00I7.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>jms-00I7</addr>  <route>jms-00I7.xml</route> <date><year>2024</year> <month>1</month> <day>17</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> <contributor><link href="marcelofiore.xml" type="local" marcelofiore="addr">Marcelo Fiore</link></contributor></authors> <title>Relation</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A <em><strong>(binary) relation</strong></em> <tex>R</tex> from a set <tex>A</tex> to a set <tex>B</tex>, written <tex>R \colon  A \mathbin { \nrightarrow }  B</tex> or <tex>R \in   \mathrm {Rel} { \mathopen {} \left ( A,B \right ) \mathclose {}}</tex> is defined to be a subset <tex>R \subseteq  A \times  B</tex>. We shall typically write <tex>a \mathrel {R}b</tex> for <tex>{ \mathopen {} \left ( a,b \right ) \mathclose {}} \in  R</tex>. More generally, a <em><strong>relation between multiple sets</strong></em> <tex>{ \mathopen {} \left ( A_i \right ) \mathclose {}} _{i \in  I}</tex> is defined to be a subset of the cartesian product <tex>\prod _{i \in  I} A_i</tex>.</p></mainmatter> </tree></related> <backlinks><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>642</anchor> <rss>jms-00IL.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Exercise</taxon> <addr>jms-00IL</addr>  <route>jms-00IL.xml</route> <date><year>2024</year> <month>1</month> <day>17</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> <contributor><link href="marcelofiore.xml" type="local" marcelofiore="addr">Marcelo Fiore</link></contributor></authors> <title>An internal diagram</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Draw the <link href="jms-00IK.xml" type="local" addr="jms-00IK" title="Internal diagrams of relations">internal diagram</link> corresponding to the following <link href="jms-00I7.xml" type="local" addr="jms-00I7" title="Relation">relation</link>:</p><tex display="block">
  \begin {aligned}
   S&amp; \colon \mathbb {Z} \mathbin { \nrightarrow } \mathbb {Z} \\ 
   S&amp;=  { \mathopen {} \left \{ 
     { \mathopen {} \left ( 1,0 \right ) \mathclose {}} ,
     { \mathopen {} \left ( 1,2 \right ) \mathclose {}} ,
     { \mathopen {} \left ( 2,1 \right ) \mathclose {}} ,
     { \mathopen {} \left ( 2,3 \right ) \mathclose {}} 
    \right \} \mathclose {}} 
  \end {aligned}
</tex></mainmatter> </tree></backlinks> <references/></backmatter></tree>